block content
	.container
		.row
			.col-lg-9
				h3 Why?
				
				p Postcodes.io is a project to make freely available Postcode data easier to consume and available at a fair price (free).

				p This API is designed for primarily for developers who want to link UK postcodes to location data ([reverse] geocoding) and to lookup basic information on postcodes.

				h3 Github
				p For bugs or feature requests use our
					a(href="https://github.com/ideal-postcodes/postcodes.io/issues") Github issue tracker 
					| or make a pull request.

				h3 Not to be confused with...

				p 
					a(href="www.postcode.io") PostCode.io
					| , a laudable, mission driven, California-based company that provides technology applications and services to local governments.

				h3 Support
				p Got questions or want to get in contact with us?
				p Chat: 
					a(href="http://webchat.freenode.net/?channels=ideal-postcodes", target="_blank") irc.Freenode.net #ideal-postcodes
				p Email: team@postcodes.io
				p Twitter: 
					a(href="https://twitter.com/idealpostcodes") @IdealPostcodes

				h3 Data

				p This API currently uses ONSPD data released in February 2014. Beyond that date, new postcodes may be added or amended and will not be captured until the its quarterly update.

				h3 License

				p Postcodes.io is available under the MIT License

				p Great Britain postcode data may be used under the terms of the OS OpenData licence. Northern Ireland postcode data may be used under the terms of the ONSPD licence

				p This API uses Royal Mail and Ordnance Survey data © Crown copyright and database right 2014 and Office for National Statistics data © Crown copyright and database right 2014 (ONSPD).
